text.section:
Each society shall:
secure bona fide applications for death benefits in an aggregate amount of at least $500,000 on at least 500 lives;
receive from each applicant evidence of insurability satisfactory to the society;
have on file certificates of examination or acceptable declarations of insurability approved by the society's chief medical examiner;
collect from each applicant the amount of at least one regular monthly premium under the society's table of rates as provided by the society's laws, and issue to each applicant a receipt for the amount received;
collect premiums as provided in item (4) of this subsection in an aggregate amount of at least $150,000 and credit the premiums to the funds from which benefits are to be paid;
establish at least ten subordinate lodges or branches into which the applicants are admitted;
submit to the Commissioner, under the oath of the president, secretary, or an equivalent officer of the society, the name, address, date of admission, and amounts of benefits and premiums of each applicant, and the name and number of the subordinate branch of which the applicant is a member; and
submit to the Commissioner, under oath of the treasurer or an equivalent officer of the society, a statement that at least 500 applicants have paid the premiums required by items (4) and (5) of this subsection.
